      <text>8.1.17 (Which geo seq are converging?)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="noindent">Which of the following geometric sequences converge to a limit?</p>  
 [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="noindent">In order for the geometric sequence to converge to a limit, we need \(-1&lt;r\leq1\). This is because:</p><p class="noindent"></p><ul><li>if \(|r|&gt;1\) then the terms are increasing in absolute value as \(n\) increases,</li><li>if \(r=-1\) then the terms are alternating between \(a\) and \(-a\),</li><li>if \(|r|&lt;1\) then the terms are getting closer to 0 in magnitude (hence converging to 0),</li><li>if \(r=1\) then the sequence is constant (hence converging to \(a\)).</li></ul><p></p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
